author: James Richings
title: Palestine fundraiser to take place in Wycombe on New Year's Eve | Bucks Free Press
text: An event to support those impacted by the ongoing conflict in Gaza will take place in High Wycombe. The fundraiser, which has been set up to help Palestinians, will be hosted at the Hive within the town on New Yearâ€™s Eve (Sunday, December 31). [READ MORE: The biggest Bucks crime story of 2023: The murder of Cameron Bailey in High Wycombe](https://www.bucksfreepress.co.uk/news/23973687.cameron-bailey-wycombe-murder-case---know-far/) Items on sale include cakes, sweets, karak chai and honey, whilst those in attendance can also receive mehndi and face painting. Handmade items will also be on sale with all the money raised going towards the WISE Welfare Gaza Appeal. It will start at 2pm, finish at 7pm and male and females will be segregated.
